news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance aims AUM of over Rs 25,000 crore by March 25
news.para: "We closed the first half with the AUM of Rs 22,817 crore (from Rs 18,885 crore as of September 30, 2023). Going by the growth rate of 23-24 per cent, AUM should increase to Rs 25,000-26,000 crore by the end of March 2025," said Aadhar Housing Finance, MD and CEO Rishi Anand.

news.title: Gujarat: Deadline to submit objections to jantri rates extended till Jan 20
news.para: The state govt announced draft proposed jantri rates and invited online objections for a month until Dec 20. However, the demand for an increased time limit and offline submission was raised by developers and farmers' groups across the state.

news.title: Lucknow development body's societies to get rooftop solar plants
news.para: The estimated cost for these solar power plants is around Rs 4.5 crore. However, the long-term benefits are substantial, with potential savings of 70-80% on electricity bills.

news.title: Gurugram development body starts survey to identify squatters
news.para: During the inspection of Nathupur Road, U and S Blocks of DLF Phase 3, officials found widespread encroachments—portions of the road, as wide as 10 feet and illegal extensions of buildings were also found.

news.title: Odisha initiates application process for PMAY-Urban 2.0
news.para: In a letter to the municipal commissioners and executive officers of the ULBs, Odisha Housing Urban Mission Director, Gangadhar Nayak, asked them to create clear and adequate awareness among the applicants and facilitate them to ensure maximum coverage under the scheme.

news.title: MREAT modifies MahaRERA order on interest to home buyer
news.para: The MREAT said that the reason assigned by the Authority is contrary to the provisions of Section 18 of RERA Act 2016 and it defeats the very object of RERA Act 2016.

news.title: Mumbai: Ornate Spaces' director denied bail in Rs 400 crore money laundering case
news.para: On Jan 3, 2024, Enforcement Directorate (ED) arrested Machinder in the money-laundering case based on a complaint lodged by an investor accusing the company of selling seven of 14 flats booked in Grove Tower in Oshiwara to others.

news.title: Gujarat government to notify nine new civic bodies in two weeks
news.para: The municipalities which will get municipal corporation status include Gandhidham, Surendranagar, Porbandar, Vapi, Navsari, Mehsana, Morbi, Nadiad and Anand. This will take the total number of municipal corporations in Gujarat to 17.

news.title: Shanghai Stock Exchange to impose self-regulatory measures on China's Country Garden
news.para: The Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange have also made the decision to impose self-regulatory measures on Country Garden Real Estate, a unit of the company, due to the failure to publish the annual report.

news.title: Maharashtra government selects 10 cities for Rs 5,000 crore urban land records digitization project
news.para: "Urban areas lack a record of rights and rely only on property tax and sale deed documents. The new system will provide clear property details or record of rights that will be updated on a dedicated portal," deputy director of land records Rajendra Gole said on Friday.

news.title: Pune civic body to issue show cause notices to construction sites over air pollution
news.para: According to the municipal corporation officials, pollution levels increased in the city because of civil works across the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) areas.

news.title: Maharashtra property registration target may rise by Rs 5,000 crore to fund govt schemes
news.para: "We've achieved nearly 64% of our Rs55,000-crore target before December. After the new govt formation, we're anticipating a target revision," a senior property registration department official said.

news.title: Karnataka government approves OTS scheme for defaulting stone quarry owners
news.para: HK Patil, minister for law and parliamentary affairs, revealed the cabinet cleared a proposal to hike mining royalty from Rs 70 per ton to Rs 80. He said the hike would result in an additional revenue of Rs 311.5 crore to the state exchequer.

news.title: Govt conducting statewide survey for PM awas yojana: Rabi Narayan Naik, Odisha minister
news.para: Pointing that thousands of people have got pucca houses under the scheme in Uttarakhand, CM Dhami said the state government is also providing assistance along with the Centre.

news.title: Nagpur civic body's Lakadganj zone attaches four properties over Rs 5.36 lakh tax dues
news.para: These property owners did not clear their dues for the period 2016 to 2024. Additionally, the zone issued notices to 798 other property owners for defaulting on property tax payments totalling Rs2.83 crore.

news.title: Bokaro DC issues show cause notices to circle officers over pending land mutations
news.para: ​​Following this, a show cause notice was issued to the circle officers of all nine blocks, along with their respective revenue sub-inspectors and circle inspectors.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body seals over 1,000 properties for Rs 362 crore tax dues
news.para: Out of the 3,500 properties, 1,900 have reached tax arrears above Rs5 lakh and 1,648 have reached arrears over Rs 3 lakh

news.title: Karnataka government yet to sign MoA for PM awas yojana: MP Brijesh Chowta
news.para: The MP informed Parliament during the session that the Karnataka govt is yet to sign the MoA to identify beneficiaries for the scheme.

news.title: Union cabinet approves Rithala-Kundli corridor for Delhi metro's phase-IV project
news.para: This line will be an extension of the operational Shaheed Sthal (New Bus Adda)-Rithala (Red Line) corridor and will boost connectivity in the northwestern parts of Delhi, such as Narela, Bawana and parts of Rohini.

news.title: Karnataka cabinet approves Bengaluru metro's phase 3A line from Sarjapur to Hebbal
news.para: The 36.6km line will have an elevated corridor of 22.1km with 17 stations and a 14.5km underground stretch with 11 stations.
